                                                         Jun 23 1995
                                                                Sony

Dear 4:2:2 profile conformance testing AHG members,

This bitstream is created for the 4:2:2 profile conformance testing.
Parameters of the bitstream "sony_422_id01-1" are the following:

Bitstream ID:  1.
Description:   Frame coded picture, B-directional macroblock predictions
               in field mode.
Stresses:      prediction bandwidth
Justification: field MB predictions in frame pictures have the largest 
               prediction bandwidth overhead
Organizations: Sony
Parameters:     
	
        Bitstream file			sony_422_id01-1.bs
        Reconstructed frames		sony_422_id01-1.pict
	Trace file of Picture Layer	sony_422_id01-1.trace

	Bit rate:               50 Mbit/sec 
	Sampling dimensions:    720 x 512  29.97 Hz 
	Number of frames:	73 frames 
	IDCT:                   double precision
        
        *frame format:

	4:2:2 frame ("display" order) 8 bit

                   <--------width--------->
                  +------------------------+
                  |                        |      ^
                  |                        |      |
                  |                        |      |
                  |                        |      |
                  |     Luminance Pels     |    height
                  |                        |      |
                  |                        |      |
                  |                        |      V
                  +-----------+------------+
                  |           |      ^
                  |           |      |
                  |           |      |
                  |  Cb pels  |    height
                  |           |      |
                  |           |      |
                  |           |      V
                  +-----------+      -
                  |           |      ^
                  |           |      |
                  |           |      |
                  |  Cr pels  |    height
                  |           |      |
                  |           |      |
                  |           |      V
                  +-----------+      -
                   <-width/2->



Please check that you can decode it.  Thank-you.

	Best regards,

